entry.title: Masses of Migrants Overwhelm Panama's Darién Gap
entry.content: Record numbers of migrants are punching through the remote heart of Emberá-Wounaan jungle territory, resulting in mountains of trash, human waste and a surge in violence and deaths.

entry.title: What's Happening With Wagner in Russia?
entry.content: Wagner chief Yevgeny Prigozhin pulled back his forces from the brink of a bloody clash with the Russian army in Moscow that threatened to plunge the country into civil war.

entry.title: Greek Conservatives Score Decisive Election Win
entry.content: Kyriakos Mitsotakis, head of the conservative New Democracy party and Greek prime minister for the past four years, is expected to be sworn in Monday for a second term.

entry.title: Why Wagner Chief Prigozhin Turned Against Putin
entry.content: Military infighting, financial pressures and personal political ambitions played into the brash decision.

entry.title: After Weekend of Chaos in Russia, Questions Remain Over Fate of Wagner
entry.content: With both Vladimir Putin and Yevgeny Prigozhin silent, Russians and Western officials wonder whether the crisis is truly over.
